Former Chancellor Helmut Kohl of Germany has passed away at his boyhood home in Ludwigshafen. As the longest serving Chancellor in modern German history, Kohl played a pivotal role in leading Germany through sixteen years of important changes. He is widely recognized as the father of German reunification and was also a strong advocate for Europe and the transatlantic relationship. The world has greatly benefited from his vision and efforts, and his legacy will continue to live on.